President Donald J. Trump has declared a state of emergency in Louisiana due to the emergency conditions resulting from Tropical Storms Laura and Marco. This declaration authorizes the Department of Homeland Security and FEMA to coordinate disaster relief efforts to alleviate hardship and suffering caused by the emergency. Public assistance, including evacuation and shelter support, will be provided for various parishes in Louisiana. John E. Long has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, media should contact the FEMA News Desk.